    "body": "Sorry for not adding a test. I didn't report an issue or looked for an open one. Just fixed it straight away. See a simple testcase below:\n\n``` python\nfrom pandas import DataFrame\nfrom numpy import NaN\ndf = DataFrame({'A': [1,2,3,5]})\n\n# interpolation with 'limit' argument gives error when there are no nan values in the series:\ndf.interpolate(limit=1)\n\n# after adding a NaN value, no error\ndf.loc[1] = NaN\ndf.interpolate(limit=1)\n```\n"
